               <head>History of Yusufza'i tribe</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tārīkh-i Ḥāfiẓ Raḥmat Khān by Ḥāfiẓ Muḥammad Ṣiddīq</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85149528 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3733-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7147">Ḥāfiẓ Muḥammad Ṣiddīq</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7147">حافظ محمّد صدّيق</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21827">Tārīkh-i Ḥāfiẓ Raḥmat Khān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21827">تٲريخ حافظ رحمت خانى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Abridged and recast Persian translation of an original Pashtu history of the Yūsufzaʾī tribe of Afghans and their conquest of the Kabul, Bajaur, Swat, Peshawar, and Langarkot districts, begun at the suggestion of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_63646020" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/no99061152" role="pat">Hafiz Rahmat Khan</persName> at Pilibhit
                        </p>
                        <p>The Pashtun historian is identified simply as Khvājū, <q>a celebrated historian and genealogist of "that" time</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into 8 majlis</p>
                        <p>Folio 1r: seal of Muḥammad Ṣibghat Allāh Khān dated <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">1182</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian">1768-9</date>, with inscriptions dated <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">1188</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian">1774-5</date> and <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">1192</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian">1778</date>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
